<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-31T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/865a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-31T18:00:00-05:00">January 31, 1934—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>14. For Reuben Clark from the Executive [Committee of] Council: No. 8.
                            Kindly advise status proposed decree. Are you sailing February 1 as
                            planned?</p>
                        <p>For Gibson: In event Clark’s departure before arrival this cable can you
                            inform Council through Department regarding preceding?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>